The paper deals with distributed computing systems, which are typically studied in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also discusses communication load and storage space, which are topics covered in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper proposes a new coded scheme, which involves coding theory, a topic covered in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses tradeoffs between different parameters, which is a topic covered in the Cryptography and Security (cs.CC) sub-category.
